# Design Generation History — Implementation Plan

This feature saves the history of each design generation (prompt, classification, and output UI schema) so that users can instantly load, review, and make further changes to past designs. It includes persistent database storage on the backend and a robust fallback to local storage on the client.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Automatic Database Saving**: When a user generates a layout, the system will automatically save it to their persistent history if they are logged in. 
> 
> **Resiliency Fallback**: If the database migration is not yet run or PostgreSQL is temporarily unavailable, the system will gracefully fall back to storing history in the user's browser `localStorage`. This ensures zero downtime or blocking errors for the generation workflow.

